\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid6966535 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me where your father came from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I can't, no
. From Manchester, I expect. Although he tells me about ... well, me father, he tells me about me grandfather having a little barrel of brandy sent from France.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 As if he might have come from France?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. Hennessey's brandy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't belong to the Hennessey brandy family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
I think he did. I think it is. But he said he couldn't pay the duty on it and they had to send it back. That's all I know about it, I mean to say, it might be hearsay, and I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You don't know where your mother came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, I haven't the fa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 intest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you know where your mother worked before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. That's one think I never used to worry about because ... well, me mother was always at home. I never used to worry about work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 She didn't work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can I ask you about your life as a child; where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. New Berg Street, Miles Platting. It changed to Ollerton Street and now it's all ... the district's all gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why was it changed to Ollerton Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me how many rooms there were in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Only 2 bedrooms. Two up and two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So where would you eat, and where would you cook, and ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 , then there was the back kitchen where they had the old boiler, wash boilers with a little barrel underneath. And there's only 2 bedrooms, pushed here and pushed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So where would your mother cook? She'd cook in the back. Do you know if she had a range or if she had gas in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No, we didn't gas in there 'till ... we didn't have gas stove 'til around about ... and it was only a grill that had about ... oh, it must have been about 1912 or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So she cooked on a range, then, before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Me mother didn't. No, me mother's died, then, before we got that. Me mother died in 1910. Oh, we were all young, yes. All young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did anyone else beside the family live in the house? Did you have relatives or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So you just had 2 bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Me mother and father; then me mother died, then a year afterwards me youngest sister died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me how the sleeping arrangements were worked out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, that's what I'm saying
. We used to have 2 beds but there was hardly any room to get 3 in a bed, as children, you know. And sometimes you had a single bed in your parents' room. The two young kiddies would be in the parents' room, very likely, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So you had to wangle it round any way that you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your mother have any help in the house, paid help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. I used to run from ... when me mother was ill with consumption I used to go from Miles Platting, and as a kid, nine year old, I 
used to walk all the way down to Ancoats Hospital to get what you call Scott's Emulsion, a medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It had a picture of a fish on the front, if I remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That's right. And I used to have to walk down there, all that way, no tram fair, no buse
s then, it was on Shank's pony to get it. And then she died in 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember much about your mother's illness, did she go in hospital or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, hospital, no. I've got ... I know it, and yet at the same time as just a boy
 you don't see it the same although you used to be there watching all the time. And there's another thing that took my eye when me mother died at that time me used to have, all the curtains all round, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Round the bed, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, when 
she was laid out. See, the body was laid out there, and the curtains coming round there - this is the old style - and a little table there with the candles on, the sideboard over there, and I was only a kid, ten. Well, I used to sit on that chair watching
 them candles like that. I was terrified of the curtains and I were a ten-year-old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I saw them place a saucer of salt underneath the corpse to take the smell away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, did they? I've never heard of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember them putting salt on the stomach?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, not actually on the stomach, but underneath. Underneath the corpse, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember going to a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I remember me mother's, and me sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Who attended, do you remember, and what they wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well ... Oh, it was all black, then, all black, and you used to have little handkerchiefs black bordered. Oh, it used to be all like that. Going on to the other subjects, same as
 the social life, you had no money for the dance hall or anything like that, there weren't such a thing them days, but the old barrel organ'd come round. And if they'd got one of them in the street they'd all be dancing in the street and they'd give him a
 bob or two and give him plenty of beer. They'd be dancing up and down the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember anything about funerals particularly, though? You know, what went on and the procedure at funerals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, as I say ..... that has been so, yes, al
ways a big respect for people like that. The same thing applied, going out of life, coming into life. Your wife'd be expecting ... no doctors, then. Bring Mrs. Murphy in, or something like that. A child was born ... everything like that. No doctors, no mi
d
wives, then. You know, they didn't have the money. They didn't have the money, like, that's the big argument. Now, me dad was a skilled engineer and at 19 ... nineteen-year-old things was bad in their trade - I was working at the Gas works. I was putting 
80 hours a week in and I was getting good money. That's what the hours I was putting in, over 80 hours a week. That was a 12-hour shift.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was before 1918, of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, 1918 - 1919. Yes, well, before 1918, yes. I started there when I was 16.
 And we never used to think about the hours we put in, and it was rough, hard work. And then we'd come out at night time and go to a dance ... well, I didn't go to a dance, I didn't do any dancing ... and have a game of football, or something like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 There wasn't any other place to do it, was there? Do you know if your mother used to make or mend any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, she did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What about your father mending shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Definitely. And he told me how to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you also tell me when you got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Whit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32486\charrsid2567301 Week.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 Whit week, more or less, and then there's a lot of families then got clothes for Whit Week and then they was put in pawn and they never see them again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me more about the pawn shops and what you remember about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Pawn shops was common. Pretty common, very common, there's no doubt about it. And I've seen people go ... it's a crying shame, really
, what's gone in pawn and then they've not been able to redeem them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And they've just lost it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
And sometimes you put ... say you couldn't get 'em out this week so you put a penny, twopence on that ticket so's it'd keep you in. And that's what it used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And they could go on paying indefinitely, could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, so long as they paid that penny or twopence on that so's it's ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, when would the man eventually sell something in a pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, in twelvemonth, I think
, round about the twelvemonth. The Gas Works, wintertime would be their busy job, and men'd be working at the Gas Works, and then when it got to about March they'd close the plants down and they'd be out, then, you'd just go and enroll on the clay tips th
en, and they'd go as navies (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Pretend they were navies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. They'd get the jobs, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can I ask you if your father helped your mother with any of the job around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, as far as I know, he did do. He was a pretty good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He was good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He was strict, but when I look back he was not as strict as ... I asked for what I got (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you get punished for if he punished you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, if I'd done anything wrong. When I asked if there was any bread left ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me that story again now we're talking on tape, the story about the bread? Incident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That I got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, that you got punished for? Well, it does illustrate the things that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I was playing on Miles Platting Station approach \{BLANK\}
 with another pal and some lad higher up asking if there were any bread left and I forget about me Dad coming from Ashdown, so I got a belt across me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 ear hole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 . 'What's that for, Dad?' 'I'll give you asking if they'd any bread left, now go off home'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You saw a lot of children hungry and asking for bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh I've seen it often, yes. I've even brought bread ... I started at the Gas Works when I was 16, I've even brought bread out of there for some that's been ill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That would be 1916, wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
1916, yes. And I've seen men there, as I say, for the jobs ... I was regular, but the others was only casual. I've seen men there, stood there at 6 o'clock ... before 6 o'clock in the morning, before 2 o'clock in the af
ternoon and before 10 o'clock at night time, but out to get a shift in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And hoping they'd try and get taken on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Generally, though, when you did anything wrong who did punish you mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, me Dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Never your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. I don't think they had much reason to, but ... I wasn't bad, just a bit naughty now and again, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did you feel when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, upstairs, aye, stop upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't resent it, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not when I look back on it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you at the time, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, certainly, I would do, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your dad dress you or undress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. And he's another one ... talking about washing. Me mother ... we'd got a beer barrel for washing 
clothes in and he was bathing me in it and I got down onto me knees and I couldn't get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Where did you bath in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 In the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you remember how often you had a bath? Once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But I got down in this ... oh, 
and me dad was cursing 'how the hell am I going to get you out of here'. Anyway, eventually he did do, but my knees was sore and me back was sore. Never no more would I get down in that tub again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How many times did you have clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Only just once a week. But they didn't go out for a bath, they went in for a swim.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 In the Cut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye, that's what it was. And I were talking to another gentleman the other night and he got talking ... they lived down near }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 Canal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  Street and the coal b
oats used to go along there, the Canal, for the mills. And he said he's been diving down in bare pelts, you know what I mean when I say bare pelts, living down and getting coal and bringing it up for home. That was as a kid. That's been done not very far 
from here. And it's been done just along round here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Diving for coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, in the canal, but now the canal are all pretty full up, now. I've run up the canal here on boats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 As a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, \{BLANK\}. You've seen that, and all, haven't you? (to wife)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me if your father ever read stories to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, no. But I'll tell you what he used to do with us. More or less he used to go out at night and like his pint. He was all right as regards that, but say he went teetotal a
nd was playing dominoes - beautiful set of dominoes, he had - there was dominoes and then there was blow bobbin, ordinary empty bobbin, one at either side of table, pouff. But he used to get vexed with us because we couldn't learn how to play cards.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He liked playing cards, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
He did. He liked playing at crib. I do, now, but I couldn't ... no idea than the man in the moon how to play them cards then. Where, he liked it. But drafts and horrible little games, like Ludo, Snakes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid806828 &}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  Ladders, what have you, as kids, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But he never read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, very rarely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember him looking after you while your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, very rare me mother was out. To my knowledge it was sickness more than anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 She never went out on her own? To enjoy herself, for anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, we was the first ones down there to have a wall clock and we used to have to leave ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What kind of a wall clock, a winding up wall clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, a pendulum, 
you know, a pendulum. We used to have to leave the front door open so's everybody could see the time, or otherwise 'knock-knock, what time is it, Mrs. Hennessey? That was so, and it seems that photograph you've seen of me mother, talk about Queen Mary. Sh
e was in red velvet, a red velvet dress, oh, gorgeous, and a stiff ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was the picture of your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Yes, and it was all, like, buttons, umpteen buttons all the way down and then just a dress watch, and I'd like to know where that's gone. Oh, it was a beautiful thing, all engraved gold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me if you had any jobs to do at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I've done the lot. Washing, the lot. She's had a lot of sickness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, I mean as a child, this is. As a child at home did you have anything ...?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I used to take pride in black leading the fire grates, stoning the back kitchen, burn moulding the hearth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, it used to be what they call a blue mould. It was like a light blue and I used to put fancy designs on t
he hearth with that. Brown stone and white stone for the other part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was this while your mother was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, this was after she died. I hadn't much to do, then, not as a kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you help with the other children, or did the children help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye, I had a lot to do there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But did you help each other with dressing or washing, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, at that age they didn't need it, really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember what time you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, oh, I do that! N
o stopping up for us, soon as it went dark barring at winter time, they we'd stop in playing games, when we couldn't go out playing. And we always had to be in at such a time, even when we was getting on. Especially me sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember what time you went to bed when you went to school, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 About 7 or 8 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you always put yourselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What about before you were old enough, who put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, it was Mum, really, not Dad because, I mea
n to say, you're going now, it's up to 10. As I say, she had a lot of sickness, but I can remember me aunt used to come over a lot and I used to remember what day me aunt bakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 A lovely muffin (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 She used to make muffins, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not half!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have a lot of relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, that neighbourliness there. Anybody's sick they'd ... or go and make a bowl of gruel, or if you was lucky enough to have a chicken, a chicken broth or something like. Oh, ah, lots of help. You'd never need to go running errands, now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember anyone helping in your house while your mother was sick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Me aunt.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They lived nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And did you visit them and they visit you ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Or did you just go casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, every well, the children'd be down for their Saturday halfpenny or their Saturday penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did your parents think of swearing when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Never heard it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Nor did they allow you to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Never heard me, and the children haven't. And I can do and I have done, at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When grownups were talking when you were a child were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, you had to keep your place. You were seen and not heard. And at the table you had to ask to leave the table before you could leave.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I was going to ask this, did you ask to leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 If you wanted something on the table could you ask for it, or did you have to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, you'd to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Now, I know you enjoyed your auntie's muffins; tell me about your food when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, the food more or less was more on the same pattern then days. You'd have a roast at weekend; you might have it cold, a resurrection day Monday, and then Tuesday it'd be hashed up if there was any left (laughter). That's what it used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How many times a week would you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We were all right for meat you see. That's what I say, Dad'd ... he used to go and do the shopping j
ust the same, he'd take me with him and he was well in with the butcher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 plenty there to go on. The only one thing I didn't like with me Dad when he stood at the table, he'd put mustard on his meat and slap the spoon across me face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Joking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He'd put it right on me lips, mustard ooh!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember what you had for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, Sunday ... this is shortly after me mother died, and all, see the difference again, you see. As I say, we had no stoves, there was only the oven. And me Dad, you'd always see him Sunday morning - he didn't go to church very much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 himself}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 but he always saw that we went - and then when we come home from church, egg and bacon fried in the oven on a plate, and the difference it tasted then! There's no taste in this stuff now at all to what there used to be.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So you used to have bacon and egg on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Sunday morning, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What during the week, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, brown bread and jam, there were no bacon nor now like that during the week. B
ut one thing we was only talking about, and we used to enjoy it, bread and dripping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 For breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Yes. Because the dripping then, in them days, was dripping and you could taste it, especially when you got down to the bottom to the jelly part. 
Get and make some toast and put some of that on it and it used to be lovely. One thing you don't see much. No, I was telling you about geese at Christmas, we used to like one of them. And then when she used to save the goose grease - 'have you got any goo
se grease, Mrs. Hennessey, the children's chests have been bad'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your mother, when she was able, make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did she make jam or pickles or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, well, no. I can because I used to have to go for it
 and I've seen them standing in a mug, big earthenware mug in front of the fire doing about a dozen of flour, or something like that, and I've actually played with a little of it meself, then put a towel over it, let it rise, then you start the bread tins
, then. Oh, aye, but I used to like the old muffins best, just with plenty of butter on them, you know, lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 She didn't make jam, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did she ever make her own medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, more or less, it was summertime. Me dad'd do it more than me mother. Thick Spanish and Senna pods stewed up together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 As a sort of laxative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, especially springtime. Oh, and then the other medicine I used to detest was brimstone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid806828 
&}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  treacle, they used to call it. Oh, it used to sicken me that did. Brimstone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid806828 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 treacle, more like sulphur than owt else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did anyone ever make beer or wine in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, tried making wine. I've not seen me own family, no. The aunt done. She's made all her own pickles and all jams, all the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But your mother didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I forgot to ask you, what did you have for tea? What was your usual tea meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, dinner, we didn't have a dinner. You see, they'd be out at work and I'd be at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I see, this was after your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. And I'd have a cake for me dinner, and then I'd have dinner ready for them coming home from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, you used to cook the dinner while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I made hotpots, 11 year old. I'd cut meats up and the potatoes and carrots and what have you, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Have it ready for them coming in ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, don't worry about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So really the dinner was made at night. Did you ever keep any livestock, goats or pigs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, no. There was no room to keep a cat, never mind ... (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 There was only 2 up and 2 down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you in those days ever get any meat from poaching, such as rabbit? But didn't get any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, we was too far in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, I don't think we got to that extreme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It wouldn't be necessary, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Could you choose what you wanted, or did you have to have what you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Had what you were given, and then you had to clean your plate, or there was no pudding for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, you used to have puddings as well, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember the type of puddings you had as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
More or less, rice pudding, or sago pudding. But there's another thing, we was only talking about it the other night a lot of people never heard about it; bread pudding.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I've heard of bread puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Instead of bread being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 wasted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  that's got stale. You put it in a dish, throw a handful of currants in with it, put it in the oven; bread pudding. It used to be nice, and all. Perhaps some treacle with it, and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, if it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way, and did you sit at a special place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We didn't sit. We had to stand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You had to stand, did you, at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, because there was ... let's see ... we couldn't all get the chairs up. We used to stand. All right. Don't worry about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you taught to use your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 All the family were all round the table together for a meal, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your father used to have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
You see, me Dad ... In those days then, the majority of people was all on 12 hours. They all started at 6 o'clock, the majority of manual workers, bar office wo
rkers. The majority started work at 6. He's got to be at Ashdown at 6 o'clock. And I've been the same, on me first day of work I've been up hauling wood in the mill. But I didn't like the mill, I soon chucked that. They always took the ... always had a sp
otted handkerchief and the bread, the snack, wrapped in that. Oh, aye. Or a basket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Your father took it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, always a red spotted handkerchief, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember when the children were little, who fed them and where they sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I were the youngest, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was your mum and easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye, she did. And there's another point one time, talking about families knowing families. One time the wife and I was having a drink a
nd these 3 ladies, all on their own \{BLANK\}
 was talking and I started laughing. And yet there was a bell ringing somewhere and one of them said to me, she said 'Oh, you're too young to remember that'. I said, 'I don't know, 'I said. 'I remember me mother p
laying skipping ropes in New Berg Street'. 'Oh, 'she says, 'who are you?' A few streets round about, good heavens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 She knew more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 . Had a g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 ramophone with a big trumpet fastened on to the ceiling ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The trumpet was on the ceiling, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It were
 fastened on there it was that big, and these cylinder little records, not these flat ones. Oh, we used to stand outside that door many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was your father easy to talk to, Mr. Hennessey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Could you share your worries with your mum and your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye, yes. He was all right. I'm trying to think, now. ... a point, but you must be up to a point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your father show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, not a great lot of love, sort of style, but same as when I were getting into 13 or
 14 I went to the barber, something like that, I was going to play football at school. He'd come and watch us, and all such as that. And then, as kiddies then you had to make your own fun. No telly, no radio.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What games did you play, do you remember your games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, definitely. I've seen us play many a time for hours on end with a piece of clay, what we used to call Flip-Flops. You'd make it round and hollow it out and you'd get it in your hand and bang it on the floor - flop. Sit there making cup
s and saucers, cottage loaves, with clay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, you always had to be careful when you went it (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Where did you play, though, did you play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 In the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Who did you play with, were you allowed to play with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, just the neighbours round, but your own neighbours' children, you see, we was all there together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was there ever anyone you were told not to play with, for any reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, you m
ight get the odd one, you see, who was a bit of a ruffian or something like that. And then, if I went playing with them I'd get me earhole belted. And then there was all the different games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Tell me about the games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 There used to be seasons for 
them. They used to be called the other season, marble season. Then there'd be kites, flying kites; then there'd be whip and top; there'd be pig in stick; then kick can, playing a game with a can. The girls playing there with bobbles and kibs; and as I say
 modeling with clay. What was the other games we used to play? Oh, that stuggy in a buttonhole and really-oh. Play with a bit of cotton and a button on the door.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have any hobbies at all when you were at school do you remember? Did you collect anything or did you have pets, or do gardening?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, once I had a rabbit. It died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you go fishing or bicycling or anything like that when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I used ... fishing in a way, fishing never appealed to me. Bicycles, nobody had bicycles then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Now and again (laughter). Oh, we used to get on fairly well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember any one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not then, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No relatives you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No. It's been funny, really. And yet, our family. .... More or less it's funny, as I say, you get together when somebody's died. Well now, my sister, she's the one at Withenshaw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Have you ever played any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, sport. Football, and that, we was all one for games, any sport, yes. But then we used to have to play in the streets, and I've got ... I come up right across the street one time, hit a policeman, with his cape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did yo
u get on with the police, tell me? Do you remember seeing a policeman round near where you lived? What did you feel about the police, were you ever said, you know, I'll bring a policeman if you don't behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, that was common, yes. And you used to 
be frightened, then, of the policeman. The police was all 6 foot tall, something like that. And yet if you was playing football in the street - of course, he had to do it - he'd even pick the ball up, get a pen knife out of the pocket and cut the ball in 
pieces and throw it at you like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 As kids, yes. You had to go up on to the rec. and it was a tidy walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What would happen if you saw a policeman when you were playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, we used to run.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How do you think he treated the people as a whole, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Not too bad, no, the ... It was the odd ones, the drunkards, and that, that'd get that trouble. But take him on the whole he wasn't bad. I don't think so, no. Like I told you I got it right across the street, just with the cape, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 With the policeman's cape?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
That's just playing ... being a bit naughty, I suppose, same as anything else. But the way things went it weren't really too bad. But there was nowhere to play, really. No, there was nowhere to play at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No playing fields, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No. And then you'd see a lot running about in their bare feet then. I'm going back on that subject again. That was another time when they got a good hiding. 'Course, it was only clogs, then, during the week. Shoes at Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you wear clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Always ...... that'd bee too tight for you. But I wore clogs and I wore them all me life, even at work. I'd sooner wear clogs now than boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You found them more comfortable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I'm not used to 
them, you see. And clogs was common, but this day, it was a hot summer's day and the children was running about in their bare feet, I'd run about in me bare feet, I took me clogs and me stockings off. Me Dad come home in the meantime. I'd got clogs - 'I'l
l give you running out in your bare feet!'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You got into trouble for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Ooh, he was a tartar like that, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever go to theatres or anything like that? While you were at school, this is; or cinemas, or music hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, you see
, the pictures didn't start until ... what? 1910, or something like that, see. But I remember going then. But the first thing I remember going to was me eldest sister took me to a pantomime at Queens Park }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 Hippodrome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 , and it was Aladdin, and I can sing the 
song right through that I first heard there. It stuck in my mind all that time. Yes, it was that 'Meet Me Tonight in Dreamland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How much pocket money did you get from your parents, and did you get it regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. A Saturday halfpenny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 A farthing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 everlasting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  stick and a farthing of something else. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 Or I might got a ha'porth of ... we used to say ' a ha'porth or all round the shop'.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 A bit of this and a bit of that (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You always got it regularly, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, always got a Saturday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 ha'porth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When you had a birthday what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, that was just it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you get a birthday present?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't get any birthday presents at all? Didn't you have family parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What about Christmas Day, then, did you ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, Christmas party, yes. And then ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You said you had a goose on Christmas Day, I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, that was us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, that was your wage, I'm sorry. Oh, well, me Dad ... more or less, it was a piece of pork that he'd get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you do anything special on Christmas Day as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, nothing special on Christmas Day. We'd have a nice do, with decorations up and what have you, you know, but
 me Dad's time was more or less New Year's Eve, and me mother's birthday on New Year's Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, of course, so you made it a special ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Made it a special do, like, always did do, and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you get nice Christmas presents, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 Well, they was nice presents then, but they was only a sixpenny pop gun or something like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Apple, an orange and a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me what you did on New Year's Eve, then, when it was your mum's birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, well, we'd ... more or less,
 we'd be in bed. In bed, oh, aye. We'd be in bed so we got little bits out of them who was allowed to stop up. When the supper was over, straight up to bed. Then they'd start a little singsong, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was there anybody who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, we used to try and sing, but we'd no musical instruments. I tried to learn a banjo once, we had a young fellow come ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You had a banjo, you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I didn't, no, the young fellow come with a banjo on
e time and ... dear me. But it used to be all just free and easy, nobody'd take no notice. You just get up and sing and 'have another drink, go on'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever make music as a family, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye. Well, you had to do, then, that was the point. There was nothing, unless you had a piano or a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15482862\charrsid2567301 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 in the house, or some or other instrument there was nothing then, no telly, no radio, no nothing. You had to make your own fun. And your house parties then, they used to be more fun then with a house party than all your fancy do's now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you do? Did you ever play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Different games, and singing, just so you'd a bit of go all the way round, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have a lot of visitors as a family? Did you go out visiting, and have visitors back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, not ... not that we went as I was a youngster, but just after we got married, oh, never away from out our house, was there. I've seen her baking 24 hours a day. I'd got to like? (name of \{ILLEGIBLE\}) glass of beer in the
re. You know, even at that ... and do you know, I was near 34 when I took a drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't ever sign the Pledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no. As a boy I was asked many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you asked to join a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Sign the pledge, and one thing and another, you know. Oh, yes!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't have one attached to your church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You did go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, you were Roman Catholic, you told me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye, we was big church-goers then, well everybody was then more or
 less. Even in both faiths, I mean to say, not only one. They was all more or less seeing the Protestants that went to church a lot more than what they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your mother and father both go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, we'd always - we were seen ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Regularly, did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, made sure that we went, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This is how you spent your Sundays, is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, and then we'd go out for a walk, then home for dinner, then out for another walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have special clothes for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 More or less, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you allowed to play games, or did they think it was wrong?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not football. Oh, if I got caught playing football with me best boots on on a Sunday, get me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 ear hole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  clouted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was it because they thought it was wrong to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Wrong to play games, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you know what you did on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye, be watching them playing football or go and play football meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Always, as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye, always. Oh, I was football mad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you in the choir at the church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, I was, I was in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did they have any activities, the choir, apart from the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They had no activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They might go out on a ... annual drive,
 or something like that, you know, same as going as far from here as, let's say, Knutsford or something like that. You was going miles away, according to ... but you was just going a little run like that. Knutsford, aye. Good Heavens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you go to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have any Sunday School outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No, no, they didn't have. Not Sunday School. The other side do it, more than anything else. It's when they used to go out with lorries and put forms on lorries and take 'em up to a park or Bogart Hole Clough, there, bun and milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You never did this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We used to get ... \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You used to change your face with the day, you traitor! (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It was really funny the things that used to go on, al
l the Christmas to see that ... and they used to go for this cake and that sort - orange and apple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Wood Street Mission you're talking about, now, are you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I never used to go there. They used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, but you saw them go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes. And it's still going yet, to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Yes, they advertise it in the paper, yes. What activities did you have in your church, though? Did you have clubs and things like that? Were you in any of them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, the only thing ... they had a Boys' Brigade, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You were in that, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you do in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Bugle. Played the bugle, me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did they have any activities, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The priest who got the Brigade up, he got moved to Bolton, and thi
s was during the War, and all and the blackout, and that, and we went to Bolton, and coming back in the dark ... oh, dear me. Come up Rochford Road in the dark and at 9 o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was the First World War, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, First World War
, aye. Oh, dear me (laughter). Some laughing over that. Bugle and fife. We had a good fife band, then. It was a good fife band. Oh, you got cheered because they thought it was the Army coming, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Let me ask you another question. Y
ou were a Roman Catholic; can you tell me whether there was any prejudice? Can you tell me anything about it if there was any prejudice where you lived between Roman Catholics and Protestants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, not between the 2 factions in themselves, but you g
ot this odd lot. Now, same as you got Whit Week - Whit Friday, Whit Monday, see. Now the biggest ones who caused the most trouble - I'll say this for both sides - was the ones that never went near Church. That's what I say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What would happen? What was the prejudice then between your Friday and your Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, they started falling out and shouting and fighting and one thing and another, and there it would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 About the processions on Friday and the Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, oh, aye. And as I say, the people that did most of it were those that never went into churches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you experience any prejudice, though, as a Roman Catholic yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me what form it took?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, it was all the same way. It was all 
the same way. But we had some great friends near to us. It was only those 'hard cases', I call them. They was neither Catholics nor Protestants, but they thought they'd shout the world off, you know; God knows His own, and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I remember that, yes, 'God knows His Own'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Used to get under my skin, that, but just seeing them at Whit Week you'd see the others out all enjoying themselves for this rough hard core, you know ... oh, it's all senseless from the bottom of it. But take it
 now, I don't know, I don't (some remark refer to the present) all the way round.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was Grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Who did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We used to do it ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever have family prayers as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, no, we didn't. Not in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You said prayers at night in bed, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 She used to do it ... (pause switch)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 As a boy did you do it? Did you say your prayers in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 In bed (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did anybody teach you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no, only just ... you had \{BLANK\} you know, through school and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You learnt your prayers at school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It's surprising what you did learn as a youngster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 In the district }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 where}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  you lived, supposing someone did something that the people round about didn't like, can you tell me if they had any special way of showing their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, I'd be a bit too young then to regards that like that, but you could soon tell when somebody was put in the cooler, or sorts. 'You heard about Mrs. So-and-so? ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They'd all be gossiping about her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me what age you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I started about five, me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What type of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 St. Edmunds, a Roman Catholic school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you know what age you finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 14.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you know the hours you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You went a full day, did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Morning and afternoon. Nine o'clock 'till 12, and then 2 o'clock 'till half past 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Pretty much the same as it is now. It was a Church school, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were there boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, not mixed. In the infants' class, but they had ... a big school, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was it far from your home and how did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no. Walk, Shanks's pony. Always had to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did you like school? What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I never did like school, me. The only thing I didn't like school was grammar. I detested grammar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, you liked school, did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I liked school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I thought you said you didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no. The only thing I didn't like was grammar. I detested that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why? You found it very hard or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Never appealed to me. Any other, like arithmetic or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 
spelling ... Now the spelling of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  today, good Heavens, it'd drive you ... \{BLANK\} Say you go for a loaf of bread and you want full weight, they'd put it on and then you'd get 
a make-weight. They used to call it a make-weight. Some-times it used to be a bit of cake, and that's what you used to go for. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And you used to eat it on the way home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Say your parents was ... say your parents or anybody was infirm
, and that, nobody to look after them, used to be sent up to Crumsell Workhouse, which is now Crumsell Hospital.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember the workhouse yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, definitely. The old men, you used to see them all in grey corduroy suits, corduroy cap a
nd coat and trousers, and if any of them was a bit able they'd have them working in the fields.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Doing what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 For their own, like, greens, you see. The cabbage and lettuce and all like that. Because then they had a pretty big field, then, did a l
ot of their own stuff. All by their own inmates, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You don't remember anything about the guardians at all, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not as regards ... well, I had no reason to come in touch with them. But I've seen these people entrants to the workhouse.
 In fact, I've been up to the workhouse, I went up with another pal to see a relation of his that was in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When I was a boy, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember what it was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, really speaking, the same as it is now, only where the ground was all cultivated it's not. But the hospital ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You don't know how people were treated inside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, no, no. It's no use me saying I do because I wouldn't. I suppose ... rather put it this way, it'd only be e
xistence, sort of style, wouldn't it. That's the way I'd put it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They be put in a pauper's grave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That's it, yes, if nobody would come and claim them. There's the graveyard up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The paupers' graveyard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were all the children in the school from the same background as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 More or less, yes. You got a few of the odd ones, you know ... what would you call them? ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 misfits}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 , sorts of style.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And were they left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, they didn't care, the pa
rents didn't care. Of course, the pubs was open all day, then. That was a big thing. And you'd get the odd one or two that spend more money on the bear than on the children. That's where it went, with some of them. That's why you saw some of them that bad
ly done to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How do you mean 'badly done}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 \rquote ?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2567301  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Ill-treated or ill-fed, or ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Ill-fed. I'll not say ill-treated, but ill-fed. But that's my point as I keep saying. If you had coppers then you was well off, but if you didn't have coppers - and I'm say
ing coppers, it was God help you, and you could get a good meal for coppers. I've seen them myself going to the butchers, buying two or 3 bones for a penny or twopence, come home, smash 'em up, make a pan of broth with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 To get the marrow out of the bone, you say?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye, make a good stock with that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can I ask you how you felt about your teachers? How did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Good. Strict with boys, the men teachers, but the teachers, in my opinion, was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 If you did anything they didn't like how did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
They had a cane or a strap, and I used to like being sent up to the headmaster to get the strap because that didn't hurt as much as the cane (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember what they emphasised as being important in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, obedience. Oh, definitely obedience. Yes, one of the main points, that. Well, it's the same as work, now. During the heavy depression while there was a lot ... thousands out of work, I was in a good job, someone asked me (cut off tape).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So at school the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  emphasised good time-keeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, yes, I always had it in my mind ... Even at school I used to be there before time and we used to have a game of football before we went into school. And at work I were the
 same. Got these chaps, two or them .... I got 3 of them a job, and every one of them let me down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your parents take any interest in your school work? Did they ever go to the school or visit the teachers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, no, you 
see, I mean to say, take me Dad, for instance. He'd leave the house at 5 o'clock in the morning and wouldn't be back in 'till 6 o'clock at night, so there was no chance of school there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did he do with his evenings, your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, he used to 
go out and have his pint and his game of cards. Oh, there was one point actually about school, once, me sisters. I remember them putting a concert on at one time. Yes, the school had the use of these dramatic societies and the children's concerts. It just
 brought it to mind, that about concerts. And they sung ... oh, what was it, now? 'The Grecian Maids'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The Grecian Maids', yes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I was only about 7, then, something like that. I can still remember that. Oh, it's funny, but I can remember that. 'We
 are the Grecian Maids'. They all had long dresses on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever know the teachers single out some people for special treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. That has happened, and it could happen, but take them on the whole, whether it was ... not say rich and poor,
 we'll say born a bit above the other sort of style. But our teachers used to be always with you. Now, say there was a boy, say he was a good sport, good a football or a runner, they'd look after you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Always looked after those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye. Yes. Whether he was poor or not, made no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever have gangs in this school, and do your remember any children who were left out of things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Used to get the odd bully, now and again. Not gangs, not as gangs as is, not gangs as in respect as gangs now. You'd get the odd }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 bully.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  Oh, you always had that. Had a fight or two meself, probably, about that. I was always able to look after meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember a child being left out of things, and why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I see that above as much now, by being kept clean. It was done many a time, especially with the girls, and I've seen it even with boys.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 If they weren't clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, the head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Would you have stayed longer if you had had an opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I wanted to go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you? You didn't do any night school, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you think you benefited from your education, or did you have any regrets about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, to me it was just ... the most ... I'll say education ... Oh, another thing. I went \{BLANK\} then round about 13 or 14, a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 crowd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 of the lads, we joined what was then New Oldham Lads Club or Boys' Club and there we had gymnastics and one thing and another, but during wintertime they'd get certain chaps'd come and they'd take
 what they call a joinery class, or a fretwork class, or a clay modeling class, or even boot repairing class. You could go in any of them at night time, but it was something to occupy your mind. But my bit ... and I can do a little bit, but all I did was 
w
hat I learnt there. New Oldham Lads' Club, it's derelict, it's gone west. It's a shame 'cos it was a great club, that was. Used to run about 7 football teams at the time. Harriers, racing, you know and the boys'd, like, competition in between ... There's 
some going now, new ones, Ardwick Lads Club in Butter Street, round there, or is it? No, Ancoats. Yes, Ancoats, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When you were at school did you ever have a part time job to make spending money or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, it won't be a part time job. I used to go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 coal yard}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  many a time, take a bit of coal, hundredweight of coal which they could get, then, at sixpence halfpenny, sevenpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You mean for neighbours, this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, I've heard this before, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I used to have what they call a wagon, take this wagon round.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It wasn't a job, really ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It was just doing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 errands}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  for neighbours, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The only ... well, it wasn't really a job then ... but ther
e was a fish shop, a fish and chip shop in front of us - I was near 14, then - and on Fridays in the screwing machine they used to do 3 bags of potatoes. Three bags of potatoes, all in tubs ready for Saturday, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And this was for spends was it
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
I used to get a shilling and a pile of fish and chips, and a shilling to me then was like ... oh, I were a millionaire (laughter). I was that, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How old would you be when you did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Thirteen, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Just before you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I was getting a shilling then, and then I started work I used to get 6d. to spend because I only got 5 bob wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was when you first started your first full time job? What did you do as a full time job, your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I went working in town. It was more a lose-end job sort of style, you know, and then I started at mill. I didn't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What was the first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It was more errand boy more than anything else, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I was having to look after meself, see, I was only ... and me dad wouldn't have me in engineering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He wouldn't let you go in engineering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And then I tried in the mill, I didn't like that. Why didn't you take the mill I don't know, it was too }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 oppressive}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  some road, but I
 could see I wasn't going to get on there. And then I started at the railway, fell in love with that job, worked 2 days and 2 nights, then I \{BLANK\}
 pass the doctor in me eyes. They were very keen on the eyes. I started at the Gas Works and worked there ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember your various jobs and what you got paid, before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
That's what I said, I started for 5 shillings. And then ... how much did I get? ... It was only ten and odd, that's all, at 16. But yet, when I got at the Gas Works 
I were a lot better off, but I put a lot of hours in, I put 80-odd hours in and that's double the work they're doing these days there. Double the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did you get your first job when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Through the Labour Exchange, yes, you're
 correct, I did go down to the Labour Exchange and they sent for this job and I just take it, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you think about the wage, did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, to me, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Which job did you stay at the longest? Let's see what jobs did you do before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I started at Gas Works at 16.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
I started at the Railway and then I got word I hadn't passed the doctor - this is when I was 16 - and then I started directly after at the Gas Works, so the other, it's only 2 years doing the other jobs. It's nothing, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, when you started at the Gas Works you say you started for 10/6d, did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I started for more than 10/6 at the Gas Works when I was 16, as I say putting hours in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What hours did you work, do you remember, when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, it was 12 hours a shift, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 At 16?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 From 6 in the morning, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 'Till what time at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Six 'till half past 5, but on that job
 it was 6 'till 6. And then later on, on that job and then the other job, going up to 18 year old - before I was that - we were going on to work at 6 in the morning till 6 at night. Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Twelve hours on Saturday, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Wait a minute, 6 o'clock Sunday morning - 2 o'clock, back on at 10 o'clock at night 'till 6 o'clock Monday morning, then you was on Monday night, 6 o'clock 'till Tuesday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When you first started there, before 1918, how did you find it, did you think that was a fair wage for the hours you put in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, you couldn't really think of it then, not in them days, you know, but I know I was getting more money than I got at the other places, and that was the thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have holidays with pay in those days? When you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No, not when you first started, no. But you soon got it afterwards and I'll tell you what they soon altered because I went in the Army ... it was only 8 hours then ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was after the first War, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
After the first War, you started at half past 7, then, out 5 o'clock. You see, in that short space of time the hours had altered altogether.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did the boss treat you as a boy when you first started at the Gas Works, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Your employer was all right, was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, if you did your work that's like it with anybody. If you did your work and no complaint, well, there's nothing to worry about. It's not the way today, is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How did you go on in the Gas Works, you'd have a sort of foreman or something, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes. You see, there's different plants and each plant has a foreman over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you do when you first went to the Gas Works, as a boy? What was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, you won't understand it, it was all different little things, you see. It's all different little things, but it was in what they call the water gas plants, you see. Now, you wouldn't know anything about that, if I started you wouldn't u
nderstand. Now, you went from the water gas plant to the other plant which was called the horizontal plants. That's where they have machines there pushing in and out and seen men sweat there in a \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 (?) pushing the retort out or dragging them out with a rake. And there's all different machines. And it's all altered again. What they call a chain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you like your job, or did you dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It was times it was rough, but take it all through we liked it because there was quite a crew of us stuck it years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How about the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, we had some good ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You had some good times, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Had some good times and bad times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have to give any of your wage to your mother? Well, it would be your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, I was giving me dad, at 19 year old, more than what many a man was getting in wages. That was 30 shillings a week I was giving him, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 besides}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  what I had for meself, that was working at the Gas Works, then. They say if you was working at the Gas Works then you was well off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When you first started did you have to give it all to your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Good heavens, it was only 5 bob at first, when I first started work. You couldn't keep anything of that out. And that's one thing they never beli
eved in, really. To get them now at 16 years old 'well, I'm going to give you so much, and take it or lump it', it's all wrong in my opinion. Penny in the shilling, we used to get. Penny in the shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Now I know you would have preferred another typ
e of occupation, 'cos you told me you wanted to really be an engineer. Did you have to serve an apprentice-ship at the Gas Works?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you belong to a trades union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you take part in any of its activities before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, not then, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But you did later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Later on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests, or did you think they were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, the first manager I'd say was different, but the second manager, he was with us all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you describe what you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, he perhaps grew up with us before he got manager and he was a well-liked chap, and he played football with the football team and cricket, and what have you, and r
eally speaking many a time we'd call him Eddie, but if there was anybody there it'd be Mr. Davies, you know, a different thing altogether. In fact, when he finished I met him one time - because when it was \{BLANK\}
 finished him off, you see - ah, now, wait ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you feel that there was a division of interest amongst workers? Was there a great division between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I didn't, no. They used to be a great crowd down at the Gas Works some road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And a tradesman you didn't feel was any different from ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. Well, you didn't see lots of that distinction, any rate. I mean, they'd mix with one another the whole lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did full time working change your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye, aye, for a bit (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You felt you were grown up and independent for a bit, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, grown up, but not independent! Not on 5 bob a week! (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You still stayed at home after you left school, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did it change your relationship with your father, working, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Nor with your brothers and sisters, did it change your relationship with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No. Well, it all depends on the family, that's what I say, it's what
 ideas get into their head. They earn a bob or two, the lord of the land, that's the only point about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When you first started work you wouldn't be able to go to Sunday School and church and things like that because you worked Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, at first. At that time, right at first, up to being 16, that's when it started ... I used to go to church when I could do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 With shift work it would make it very difficult, wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were you ever interested in politics as you were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not to a great amount. Never have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What was the difference in how you spent your spare time when you grew up and you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well that's as I told you before, with the lads, we'd the New Oldham Lads Club, and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was while you were at the Gas Works, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no. See, you're talking about earlier than that, aren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. When you started work in your 'teens before 1918, how did you spend your spare time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh,
 I can tell you that quite easily. I never did dancing. That's one thing I never did and if I had me time over again, I would do. Me and me mates, we went to theatres, theatres, theatres. We've come out of ... Saturday nights we've come out of Manchester 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Hippodrome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  - which was Manchester }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Hippodrome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 , where the Gaumont pictures is now - first house ... they used to run 2 houses ... and we've crossed the road into Palace and gone in there the second house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you? You were keen on theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We've been in every theatre in Manchester. Oh, we was big theatre goers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you keep the same friends after you started work or did you change your friends, get different friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no, me and him, 'till we got married, didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This 'him' was a boy you were brought up with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But you kept your same friends, you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They've gone up, he's been up with the \{BLANK\} a good number of years, now, but we've always kept together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your father want to know where you were going and did you have to be in at a certain time as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I was ... to a certain age, of course. Always '... 11 o'clock, lad', something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They wanted to meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. Well, I only had the one, really. It was only Jimmy Davies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 'Till you met your wife this was, of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, and then ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't go out with other women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Me mates, me and me mates, we
 never used to bother. We never used to bother with having a drink. Theatres, theatres, theatres. Ooh, we did spend some money on theatres. And then he came across one time just before we got married, to the Isle of Man. He'd never been on holiday before.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you go on holidays as a child with your people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, not very early. Me dad had a lot of sickness and they never used to go away, then all at once he got it into his head to \{BLANK\}
 go to the Isle of Man. When he started going to the Isle of Man he never stopped going to the Isle of Man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How old would you be when you went then? Your first holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 First holiday, oh, I was getting 19. That was after I come back out of the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't go on holidays before the First War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, bar the odd day, you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Had you used to go somewhere on Bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Very rare, more it used to be ... more Bellevue or something like that. Very rare, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you go out at all with your father on your own? As a boy? They didn't usually, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I'll tell you what happened to us, we used to have to take it in turn. Saturday night me mum }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 dad would go into town and one of us would be in town with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They take one of you with them, you mean, in turn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, yes. And it would be you had to walk it, you know, no car, and it's a well way to town. Oh, aye. But the same shop's there yet, it's a little shop in ... is it Tripp Street? - off Tripp Street, a biscuit shop, and they used to sell little biscuits wit
h a little blob of toffee on the top, and we used to have a ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And this was your treat? You'd go with your parents just for a walk to town, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They'd go for a drink, or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They'd go for a drink, and there's ... I was sat one time - children was allowed in at \{BLANK\} and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you say you used to go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes. And you used to go in and it was the Wine Lodge, I can tell you where it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Yates}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 Wine Lodge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Yates}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  Wine Lodge, The Middle Wine Lodge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And you went in with them, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
And I went in with them and sat me down on a step there, and bought me a couple of cream crackers with some cheese. Oh, I was ... I was landed! (laughter) And then we'd have to walk home, save some bi
scuits for them when we got home, for me sisters. And then the following Saturday it'd be the other one's turn, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Who looked after the children who were left at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We had to look after ourselves. Of course, by then at 7 and 8 you was old enough to look after yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can I ask you if you had books or magazines in the house, or newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Yes, oh, yes. There was one ... talking about books and magazines there used to be a standing order. Comic cuts, ships. The Magnet and The Gem, every week, and I used to laugh many a time to see me dad get stuck in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Reading the comics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did he ever read out loud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, no. But me laughing at that, a funny thing I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 remember}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  when he was in the Navy
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember your mum reading out loud, or reading to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No, no, not that. It was ... me mother, really, I've got very little memory of her. There's other things outstanding in me mind. Before we moved out of that house into the other one I'd be about 6.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why did you move, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes. I'd only be about 6, from out of ... into Lodge Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember why you moved? A better house? A bigger house, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, not really bigger, it was only 2 up and 2 down, bu
t it was better situated than that. Haven't you heard people tell about doing a moonlight?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, no. You knew somebody who did it, do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, many, well nigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Go on, tell me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well at that time, then, there was houses empty about, and 
you might owe some rent and during t'night you'd just pack your traps on a hand cart and wheel away and you're living somewhere else after that. That's what they call doing a moonlight. And that was common. Yes, that was common because I can remember Oren
 Street at one time, there was 2 houses occupied in that street and it did look derelict, and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 
Not really derelict, but they looked all ... And then the First War ... and by the time the First War was over all those houses was taken, and well done, and all. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Young couples got them and done 'em up, painted them and made it look real nice. Surprising to see them houses taken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Would you say that you received your ideas about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than another?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Both played it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did they talk about how to bring you up, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No, I can't say that, but same as ... me and her's done the same. If she was to chastise one of them, well, she chastised 'em and I wouldn't take it's part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, you never took sides against them. And this happened in your house, did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This happened in our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 house?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your father take an interest in politics and did he ever talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, the Liberals were ... In fact, the L
iberals at one time was one of the best, and now it's just got between Socials and Tory, now, you see. But meself, if it was a good Liberal government I think we'd do better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever hear your father talk about politics before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes
, yes. 'Course, he was more inclined for the then Liberal, then it became Social and of course, he was for Social, then, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember why he held these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I couldn't tell you what he thought about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Your mother, did she vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
No, no. Well, really speaking, I'm quite like that because ... say there's a husband and wife, the husband goes to vote Labour, the wife vote Conservative, you might as well scrub it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember your mother ever voting, though, in an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You don't know whether she had any particular views? Your mother didn't have any views on politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, not that I knew of. There was one not very far from here, well, up to two year ago, a year ago. She was one of t
he ... one of them that was with Mrs. ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Pankhurst?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Pankhurst. What was her name, Mary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Have you heard your mother discuss this, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, me mother never used to \{BLANK\}. No, as I say, me mother died when I was 10, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their job if they voted differently from their employers? Do you think your father ever felt himself under this kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you? You felt that your father did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, you said 'did you think that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Your father ever felt under this pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, I wouldn't care to say his mind, he never spoke to me about it. But I thought that, meself. I mean to say, you're asking me to explain me dad's mind there, aren't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You don't think he ever felt under pressure to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, I wouldn't know, because he wouldn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, what were you just meaning then about ... you know someone else who was under pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, I said it has come under. I've h
eard people say 'if I don't vote for so-and-so I'll be out'. Oh yes, it could happen. It has happened. I won't put names on them, but it has happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But not to your father, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, he wouldn't say, I mean to say, politics ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He'd never discuss politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Aye. No, not as young like that, we never discussed ... Not to that extent, but it did happen and I have heard about it. When the old squire went passed on his horses - you'd have read about that yourself - you'd doff your hat and open the gate for him. 
\{BLANK\} You might be a worker but you have to doff your hat and open the gate, 'Yes, Sir'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I've asked you about your father staying home in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He didn't stay home very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, say perhaps, twice a week, something like that, all depends whether he was skint or not (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Your dad did go to a pub then. Was he in any clubs, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He was in the - what do you call them? - Buffaloes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What kind of a club was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Not a club, it's a ... certainly you've read about that!!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I've heard of the Buffaloes, but I don't know what they are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 It's some sort of a ... same as the Masonics, brethren sort of style, and the Buffaloes are the same. I k
now I've been asked many a time to join it and it never interested me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your mother ever go with him for a drink to the pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can't ever remember me mum going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Except at Yates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 At Yates, that's the only time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That wasn't quite a pub, though, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, it is. Yates Wine Lodge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Didn't they also have a teetotal ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. Ah, that was on the other side of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, I'm getting mixed up with. Yes, it was the pub at one side ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 There was 3 different Yat
es's in Oldham Street. There was Top Yates's, still there; there was Middle Yates's, still there, but the Bottom Yates's is gone, that's where Woolworth's is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, what was the difference between the 3?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No difference. Yes, that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 next door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  to the middle one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The teetotal tavern was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, that's still there, yes, and all. That's more of a caf\'e9 than ale house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, it was a caf\'e9? They also had a pub, too. Did your dad take part in any sport, or did he attend races, or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 W
ell, he used to have a bet now and again, but he didn't go to the races, he didn't have no money to go to races. He'd have a bet now and again. He used to like his game of cards, that's what I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That was his sport, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, bowling, he'd do a bit of bowling, but not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your father or mother belong to a savings club, boot club, sick club or funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Shoe club, yes. Sometimes, that name rings a bell.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The only thing you were in was a funeral club, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He wouldn't entertain like those clubs at all. Or unless he saved, himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your mother have any help outside the home to help look after the house? Families, relations? You told me your auntie came and baked.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, no. Ah, me auntie when she was ill. When she was ill, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever have any help from neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
If she was ill, say me auntie wasn't there or me cousin wasn't there, a neighbour ... as I say a neighbour, if she was sick, say make a pan of gruel, as they called 
it then. Or if they was lucky enough to have a chicken, a bit of chicken stew or ordinary stews. Just a little bit like that, you know. Or they might just do a cake for them, or something like that. But the neighbourliness was very pronounced. Very pronou
nced. There's not on the estate, now. You could be dying now and nobody knows where you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
What do you remember about it as a child in particular, though? Just this particular thing that they brought food in if you were sick, about the neighbourliness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, yes. Oh, aye, that was done a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Now, I asked you did you have relatives living nearby, didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. I told you about it just 2 or 3 streets, that lady knowing more about it than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did your parents have a lot of friends and where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You used to have people in at home, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did they come for meals or just ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, no, not for meals, just ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Call in casually, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Casually, sort of style, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were they usually your father's friends, or your mother's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, no, I can't say it was that way in our house because they didn't bring very many in at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, with your mother being sick it would ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 brought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  very few in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And I remember you told me they used to go out for a drink if they came in didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 People tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, do you remember particularly what your parents did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, as 
I said before, no piano, no nothing like that so unless you'd got some friend that had a melodeon or a banjo and they come in, you'd make a bit of a sing-song yourself. Just free and easy, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Were people allowed to call in without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, invitations weren't thought of them days, was they!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Same with neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Aye, same with neighbours. More likely than not the back doors were open. In fact, sometimes you could get annoyed at it, really, it were too much, you know. A
 bark at the back door, 'are you there, Mrs. So-and-so?' 'Have you got a cup of sugar to lend me?' (laughter) That's been done, aye. I remember me dad talking about a cat that we had, and over the mantelpiece he used to have shades, and figures, like, ove
r
 the mantelpiece on the chimney piece, and this cat got up and it went walking in between them and she was stood there, Dad saying nothing 'till he come down (laughter). Oh, dear me! And then he used to have another cat, it used to get its claw and touch 
the latch when it wanted to come in. And you needed cats, and all, down there then for mice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you have a lot of mice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, in all them houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Tell me about the living conditions, what you can remember about living conditions in your district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Nothing, really. There was nothing, really, to speak of. As I say, it was flagged .... The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  floor would be wood, but the ... that's why I was saying, me with the Venetian brownstone and brim all the hearth. Then I used to be doing th
e fire irons, brass on one side and steel on the other. I used to like doing it. Me, I don't know whether there was something wrong with me, or what. I used to like burnishing them 'till you could see your face in them. And then of a morning, summer holid
a
ys, there again I was always up early. I've been up with bucket and cloth and walked up there. I've been up there at 8 o'clock in t'morning, and walked all the way up, up round by the Black Brook, Stoney Brew, what have you. Used to be great walks then. G
reat walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You did a lot of walking, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, we did. Up to 10 year ago we both did a lot of walking. Yes, we were great walkers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups in that time before 1918. Do you think 
of some people belonging to one and some to another, and can you tell me what the different ones were? The different classes of society before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Say that with your ordinary people, no, but get some of your shopkeepers and one thing and another, t
hen you get that bit of class, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You thought the shopkeepers were better class, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They seemed to give you that impression.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why? Who did they mix with, the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, more or less they'd all, they'd go out with Mr. So-and-so from such a shop, or such a shop. Although I've seen them good mixers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember who the teachers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, well, the teachers, they all lived far away from us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What about the parsons or your priests, who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, the priests. Oh, they ... the one that was down there he was very well liked, both by Protestants and Catholics, the Very Rev. Dean Bradley. He was a gentleman, he was. A real gentleman. And he'd get at the window many a time, of the hou
se, you know, looking over the school yard with one or two oranges, throwing them down to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Throwing them to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. And some of them children might never have seen an orange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why? They would be so poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 A lot of them like that, yes. Aye. And get you could get oranges, aye, you've had 'em, maybe been going a bit ripe, six for a halfpenny.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But some of them couldn't afford them, even so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, but I mean to say, they wouldn't even go for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 ha'porth}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  of fades, what they call a ha'p'orth of fades.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 That was when the oranges were starting to fade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, and you'd cut bits off and have about 6 for a ha'p'orth what had just got ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Just cut the faded part off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, oh, aye. And me mate and me we've gon
e a ha'p'orth of broken biscuits. Good heavens, we got a bag like that. Same as they say at the chip shop, ha'p'orth of chips. We've even been to the chip shop and ... 'have you got any scrapings, please?' 'Ah, you're at it again!' This was when I was a k
i
d in New Berg Street. Talking about a thing like that, I dropped a stick down a grate and me and another lad had picked it up and I bent down and it dropped on me hand, and I remember me mother and me aunt, me Aunt Allyn taking me down to Royal Infirmary 
- which was the Royal Infirmary - down in Piccadilly. And I was only a kid then, I was a real kid. And walking all the way up Oldham Road ... you didn't have no bus fare, nor car fare or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Even though you were injured, you'd got to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Oh, yes. I was only a kid but they was trying to carry me now and again. But I remember that and I must only have been about 4, then. Must have only been about 4. I can remember that, catching my hand. And it's always been different, and all. See that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What class would you say you belonged to, yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, I won't say the poor class. No, just a bit above it. Not much, but I won't say middle class. I'd still say working class, but on the top class of the working class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What other people would you say belonged to the same class as yourself? What type of people would you say belonged to the same class?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Ah, well, there again, you see, we only got mixed up with the same working class parties. In a town it's not the same as in t
he country, you see, where there's thousands you're all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You mean you were more or less in one community all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Community all the time, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you ever remember anyone you had to call 'sir' or 'madam', or touch your cap to, or show respect in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, the only ones really was the headmaster, or the priest. But we was always taught to show respect, irrespective of who it was. Oh, yes. Yes, we was that. Any friends of me dad's come ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You always had to take your cap off too them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye. Yes, one thing we always had to show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember people showing respect to your Mum }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid806828 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  Dad in this way, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, certainly. The respect and manners them days compared to these days is different
 as chalk and cheese. There's no manners or respect these days. Very far between. Very rare hear a child say 'please' or 'thank you', now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You feel they were very courteous when you were a child, do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Definitely. And I had to be meself. And I've seen that me own children was, and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
In the district where you lived was anyone considered very important, and did you come into contact with them, and who were they? Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, not in the town, in our community, as I said before, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You don't remember anyone who was considered very important? Who was the person you thought of as the most important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You mean round our district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Round your district, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, it's the ... the main man'd be the priest from our school, the minister from St. Augustine's who was very nice, and the doctor.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you come into contact with them a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Fairly, oh fairly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You came into contact a lot with the priest, did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Fairly enough, oh, yes. And he was very nice, and all. The same one, the Dean, as married us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you tell me what sort of people went to Church and what sort of people went to Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Now, you can 
have it both ways, but to take it as people going to their own denomination, we never had any trouble with it, bar, as I said before, those people at Whit Week that kick all Hell up, but they never go near the churches. Only in name only, sort of style.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever know anyone who went to Chapel? Did you know Chapel people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 next door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  neighbour's still a ... she's sort of friends with all of 'em. But we sort of played together. Never used to have any trouble. You'd have a few 
words now and again, but not to be any, say, trouble. What had he used to call? Catholic the \{BLANK\} he'd call u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301 s, and we'd call him Proddy Dog}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  or something like that (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember any difference between Chapel people at all and Church, any distinction? In the types who went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, the only I could say used to make more distinction in both denominations, of the people with the money. They had their own pews, sort of style.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 This was in your church, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 In all churches. In all the churches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And where you lived were all the people in the working class, did they have the same standard of living as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Or were there different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 More or less the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you think that one group ever felt superior to the rest? Were there some families thought of as 'rough' and some as 'respectable'?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, you could get that. But as you say, you get some rough, they just couldn't care. Say, they could have got a new pair of shoes but th
ey didn't bother, they go and booze it or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And was there a difference in the homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Can you describe the difference at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Just only cleanliness and one thing and another, you know. It's an old s
aying with Lancashire people that the way you can tell a people's house is by the windows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And you felt this was so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 See dirty windows you'd got a dirty house. And I bet you'll always find it so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember any rough families at all, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Tell me about them, without names, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well the rough part is that little street I told you about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Which one was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 A little street called Oren Street, there was only 2 houses occupied at the time, First Wa
r. And then when the First War was over they was all occupied. And there was what they call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Badley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
 Street, they used to call it Badley Hall ... Badley Hall Terrace, they used to call it. Oh, there used to be scraps and fights there on a Saturday night (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Had there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What? Were the men drunk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Drunk! Oh, aye. Oh, it used to be common down there, then. That was a rough little quarter. That was the same as what used to happen about Angle Meadow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You said you went into Angel Meadow, did you? You knew Angel Meadow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 A little, not much. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What do you remember about it particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I know the police used to have to go to the ... No policeman went down there on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever go into it yourself? Even to go round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, it's only a little district, that's all it was, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 But you never went through Angle Meadow yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, as I say, I went through the street, but not to be down there at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why not at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Ah, well, that's when the trouble started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What kind of trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
When they got boozed up, and fighting, and one thing and another. Oh, aye. No, the policeman down there at that time, one policeman daren't go down there on his own. O
h, dear, they used to be devils for fighting. Not the same now, it's altered a lot. I'm saying it's altered a lot, I don't know that it has altered so much. You used to see some of these \{BLANK\} two or 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15089687\charrsid2567301  lived down that way}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 , but where they are now I don't know. They seem to have all scattered all over the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you remember a difference between craftsmen and labourers when you were a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The only way was by the different overalls they wore, to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Is that all, to you as a boy? Why different overalls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
There was blue for the engineers, white for the painters, blue and white ones for t'butchers. What was the other trade? What was the yellow ones? Those are the main ones, though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You didn't see any other difference as a child? No, you were too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you think your father and mother had the same attitude to people of different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I should think so. What I saw of it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a certain social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I mean to say, now and again, she died early and died when I was very young. I can't say much about her at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you think it was possible to move up from one group to another before 1918 and did you know anyone who did, you know
, go up in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I think you could have done if you got a different job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You think it was through jobs, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I think so, yes. Definitely, through jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you know anyone who did go up in the world? And how they did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Well, it's as I say, through the different jobs. As I say take me mum, that photograph. You saw that photograph, she didn't belong round here. I wish I could get that photograph. She wouldn't belong round here, but she went, and that was it. And me d
ad, he always dressed respectable. Always well dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Did you ever know anybody who went down in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, that's easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 How, though? What usually brought it about? The drink, you say, you assure me it was the drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember anyone being described as a 'real lady' or a 'real gentleman'? And why do you think this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, there we come back to me mum again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 So your mother was described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why do you think this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, her attitude, her style, and everything. I know that if I had that photograph and I'd have shown you, you'd say so, as well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember anybody else in the district being called a real lady or a real ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes, who was that? (to wife) Was it Mrs. D \{BLANK\} that had the pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 They had a pub, yes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Had a pub. Oh, she was very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why do you think she was called a real lady, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, her attitude, you see. She was nice without putting all the airs and graces on and 'I'm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 it' sort}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  of style, you know. She could do it so nice, so easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Was your home rented and did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Yes. Yes, I used to take the rent to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He used to have that Hay and Corn place on the Oldham Road. What was it? Four }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid806828 &}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  twopence, I think it was. And then he used to sell bags of peas and pigeon corn and I used to get a handful of peas and put them in me pocket for me peashooter, afterwards. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Do you ever remember feeling that your mother and father had to struggle to make ends meet, and what you felt about it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 No, I can't say as I would say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 You never had any trouble at all to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 We had a ... I suppose at times we had a rough passage but not to that extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 About the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
The police used to go to the schools and some that had been barefoot there, so they'd give them a pair of clogs or otherwise send them down to the Wood Street Mission, that's a p
lace that's going yet. And then another thing that I want to tell you about is the ... I remember going on a ... one time from the pub with me dad on a picnic, with what they call the all three, you know, the old charabanc, and we went to Knutsford and I 
thought I were in the seventh heaven of delight! Big pile of food and what have you, plenty of pop to drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 The children had pop and the men took beer, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 There was only two children there, that's all. They allowed two children to go, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why only two children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Oh, it was a men's picnic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 And you were favoured, were you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Well, there was the landlord's daughter and me dad's pal, and I was one. I were favoured, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Your dad was a pal of the landlord's so you were allowed to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12853034 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 Favoured, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
This was one of the interviews I got through the paper. There had been a lot of communication going on in the Manchester Evening News about the bad or the good old days, according to how people saw them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
This gentleman had written quite a long letter about the pawn shops and saying that people remembered them as 'good old days', but they weren't really good old days, he thought of them as bad old days. He said, as he says on the tape, t
hat it was easy, if you had the pennies to live in Manchester, but it was a matter of pennies. If you didn't have the pennies you were just unlucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I thought he could turn out to be quite an interesting respondent so I wrote to him, along with Mr. Sh
annon. I got a reply the next day saying he was very interested in the way social workers worked - I mentioned it was Sociology - and that he would be pleased to see me. So I went over to Newton Heath to interview him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I don't know whether you can tel
l by the sound of the tape, but he was a very, very hearty gentleman who insisted on moving about the room. I did ask him several times if he could sit still because of the microphone ... and he'd say 'oh, I can't sit still for very long'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 His wife was in the room during both interviews. She is suffering from Parkinson's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16732459\charrsid2567301 Disease}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301  and you will hear him keep referring to her during the course of the interview.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 He also answered, in many cases, by actions, as in the case of when I asked him if anyone e
ver went down in the world. He said very heartily, 'yes' and started to illustrate by jumping up and pretending to drink a pint of beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 I have tried as far as possible to keep recapping at this point, as he does this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 When I asked him about peop
le going down in the world he signaled to me to put the tape off - in fact, I had very great difficulty as you can hear, keeping hold of the interview at all, he more or less took charge and talked at very, very great length, and I had to keep interruptin
g
 to get questions in at all. The first afternoon I don't think I got more than a quarter of an hour on tape, the rest were all reminiscences which range from early childhood to present day. I made a note of some of them and tried to get them in, as you wi
ll hear, when I went on the second afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
Unfortunately, I found out that a lot of the reminiscences were things that he had read, so of course, I had to go back on the tape and obliterate these and then continue the interview from there. I explain
ed to him that I didn't want anything that he had read, just his own experiences.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid6966535 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6966535 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14562856\charrsid2567301 
As usual, of course, he had the idea that you wanted to know local history and I got a long list of all the buildings round about that had changed, and how many had come
 down and I had quite great difficulty to keep interrupting. You will hear that made a lot of snaps on the tape for this. I would listen patiently and watch for an opportunity to interrupt.
\par }}